Anonymous Sat 18 May 2024 21:51:13 No.65852843 Report
Quoted By:
>>65852666
>getting their systems infected
USB Rubber Ducky, it can do all kinds of nasty things if programmed correctly since the system sees it as a keyboard.
>blowing up their motherboard
USB Killer, the data lines are hooked up to capacitors that'll send a shitton of voltage down where it's not supposed to go the moment you plug it in.

If it's the former, get some offline machine you can reformat if it ends up being something nasty. If it's the latter, you could check the data lines with a multimeter, you could open it up and see if there are just capacitors instead of electronics, or you could get a dedicated safeguard adapter for verifying if you have an USB Killer or not.
